===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|pen}}, {{m|enm|penne||enclosure for animals}}, from {{inh|en|ang|penn||enclosure, fold, pen}} (in compounds), from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*pennō}}, {{m|gem-pro|*pannijō||pin, bolt, nail, tack}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*bend-||pointed peg, nail, edge}}. Akin to {{cog|ang|pennian||to close, lock, bolt}} (in compounds {{m|ang|onpennian||to open}}), {{cog|nds|pennen||to secure a door with a bolt}}, {{cog|ang|pinn||peg, bolt}}. More at {{m|en|pin}}.

Sense “prison” originally figurative extension to “enclosure for persons” (1845), later influenced by {{m|en|penitentiary||prison}}, being analyzed as an abbreviation (1884).<ref name="oetyld">{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}</ref>

